# glpi-rgsupervision-sync

GLPI plugin for automatic synchronization of **RG Supervision** alerts into GLPI tickets.

![GLPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/GLPI-10.x%20%7C%2011.x-blue)
![PHP](https://img.shields.io/badge/PHP-7.4%2B-purple)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-GPL%20v2-green)
![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/Version-1.0.0-orange)

---

## How it works

The plugin queries the RG Supervision API every 10 minutes via the GLPI cron and:

- Creates a GLPI ticket for each new open alert
- Automatically assigns the client entity via the **GLPI TAG** matching the RG node
- Determines the ticket category based on the entity's **active contracts**
- Adds a private follow-up task if the `raiseCount` counter increases
- Automatically resolves the ticket when the alert is closed on the RG side
- Detects manual reopenings and closures performed by technicians in GLPI

> **One-way synchronization** — RG Supervision → GLPI only.

---

## Requirements

- GLPI 10.x or 11.x
- PHP 7.4+ with the `curl` extension
- Network access to `api.rg-supervision.com` (HTTPS 443)

